tics gave the movie a variety of ratings. While the script and pacing drew criticism, Neel's direction, the action scenes, photography, and performances especially Yash, received accolades. In addition to this, the movie smashed domestic opening day records in the Indian languages of Malayalam, Hindi, and Kannada. It also outperformed its predecessor's lifetime gross in just two days to become the highest-grossing Kannada movie. is the second-highest-grossing movie in India and the third-highest-grossing Indian movie ever. 3. Pushpa: The Rise Pushpa was written and directed by Sukumar is an action drama movie made in the Telugu language. The film, which was made by Mythri Movie Makers in collaboration with Muttamsetty Media, stars Allu Arjun as the title character, Fahadh Faasil, and Rashmika Mandanna. Supporting roles are also played by Jagadeesh Prathap Bandari, Sunil, Rao Ramesh, Dhananjaya, Anasuya Bharadwaj, Ajay, and Aja. The first of the two films follow the rise of a coolie in a red sandalwood smuggling ring. Red sandalwood is a rare wood that can only be found in the Seshachalam Hills of the state of Andhra Pradesh. The COVID-19 epidemic forced a halt to the movie's production in March 2020, which started in December 2019. The Ramoji Film City in Hyderabad and the Maredumilli forest in Andhra Pradesh served as the primary locations for the majority of the filming, which commenced in November 2020 and ended in November 2021. Telugu and dubbed versions in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, and Hindi were both released on December 17, 2021. Critics gave the movie mixed to excellent reviews, praising Allu Arjun's portrayal and characterization, the action scenes, the directing, and the score while criticizing the length. The movie became the highest-grossing Indian movie in 2021 and is one of the all-time best-grossing Telugu movies. 4. RRR S.S. Rajamouli, who co-wrote the screenplay with V. Vijayendra Prasad, directed an epic action-drama movie in the Telugu language 