ng in Chennai in early July 2015 after post-production work and a formal launch ceremony in June 2015. The film was halted twice due to the Film Employees Federation of South India's strike and the heavy flooding in Chennai. Additionally, due to China's unfavorable weather, the production team decided against filming any sequences there and instead chose to shoot in Bangkok. Despite the challenges, the movie was finished by January 2016. 6. EEGA 2012 Indian fantasy action movie that S. S. Rajamouli wrote and directed. It was simultaneously shot in Telugu and Tamil, the latter under the title Naan Ee (I, the Fly), and was produced by Sai Korrapati's Vaaraahi Chalana Chitram with an estimated budget of 26-40 crore (US$5-7 million). Samantha, Nani, and Sudeep all appear in the movie. The score and soundtrack were written by M. M. Keeravani. The film's editor was Kotagiri Venkateswara Rao, while the director of photography was K. K. Senthil Kumar. The dialogue for the Telugu and Tamil versions was written by Janardhana Maharshi and Crazy Mohan, respectively. The plot of the movie takes the shape of a father reading his daughter a bedtime story. Its main character Nani, who is in love with his next-door neighbor Bindu, is killed by wealthy industrialist Sudeep, who has feelings for Bindu and sees Nani as a rival. In an effort to revenge for his death and defend Bindu from the obsessive Sudeep, Nani reincarnates as a housefly. The movie's two versions, together with a Malayalam-dubbed version titled Eecha, were released on July 6, 2012, in roughly 1,100 theatres around the world. Upon its debut, the cast's performances, Rajamouli's direction, and the visual effects all won praise from critics. One of the highest-grossing Telugu movies of the year was Eega. 7. Sivaji: The Boss 2007 action movie in Tamil that was produced and directed by AVM Productions. Rajinikanth and Shriya Saran are the movie's leads, and Vivek, Suman, Manivannan, and Raghuvaran also have prominent role