mic forced a halt to the movie's production in March 2020, which started in December 2019. The Ramoji Film City in Hyderabad and the Maredumilli forest in Andhra Pradesh served as the primary locations for the majority of the filming, which commenced in November 2020 and ended in November 2021. Telugu and dubbed versions in Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada, and Hindi were both released on December 17, 2021. Critics gave the movie mixed to excellent reviews, praising Allu Arjun's portrayal and characterization, the action scenes, the directing, and the score while criticizing the length. The movie became the highest-grossing Indian movie in 2021 and is one of the all-time best-grossing Telugu movies. 4. RRR S.S. Rajamouli, who co-wrote the screenplay with V. Vijayendra Prasad, directed an epic action-drama movie in the Telugu language in 2022. D.V.V. Danayya of DVV Entertainment produced it. N.T. Rama Rao Jr., Ram Charan, Alia Bhatt, Shriya Saran, Samuthirakani, Ray Stevenson, Alison Doody, and Olivia Morris are among the actors who appear in the movie. Two real-life Indian revolutionaries, Alluri Sitarama Raju (Charan) and Komaram Bheem (Rama Rao), and their struggle against the British Raj are the subjects of this fictitious tale. The story, which is set in 1920, focuses on the unrecorded period of their life when both revolutionaries decided to disappear before starting the struggle for their nation. At the time of its release, RRR was the most expensive Indian movie. In March 2018, the movie received a formal announcement. Due to delays brought on by the COVID-19 epidemic, principal photography for the movie did not finish until August 2021 in Hyderabad. With a few scenes in Ukraine and Bulgaria, the movie was primarily shot in India. M.M. Keeravani composed the soundtrack and background music for the movie, which was shot by K. K. Senthil Kumar and edited by A. Sreekar Prasad. The production designer for the movie is Sabu Cyril, and V. Srinivas Mohan oversaw the visual effects. The movie's initial release date in theatres was set for July 30, 2020, however, it was repeatedly postponed because of the pandemic and production issues. 5. Theri A 2016 Indian action thriller film in the Tamil language, which was written and directed by Atlee and was made by Kalaipuli S. Thanu under the production company V Creations. Samantha Ruth Prabhu and Vijay both appear in the movie. George C. Williams handled the cinematography for the movie, and Ruben handled the editing. G. V. Prakash Kumar created the music. The protagonist of the story is a former police officer who is out to avenge the loss of his wife while also attempting to safeguard his daughter from gangsters. Atlee wrote the script for the "emotional action thriller picture," which was formally announced in September 2014. The movie started filming in Chennai in early July 2015 after post-production work and a formal launch ceremony in June 2015. The film was halted twice due to the Film Employees Federation of South India's strike and the heavy flooding in Chennai. Additionally, due to China's unfavorable weather, the production team decided against filming any sequences there and instead chose to shoot in Bangkok. Despite the challenges, the movie was finished by January 2016. 6. EEGA 2012 Indian fantasy action movie that S. S. Rajamouli wrote and directed. It was simultaneously shot in Telugu and Tamil, the latter under the title Naan Ee (I, the Fly), and was produced by Sai Korrapati's Vaaraahi Chalana Chitram with an estimated budget of 26-40 crore (US$5-7 million). Samantha, Nani, and Sudeep all appear in the movie. The score and soundtrack were written by M. M. Keeravani. The film's editor was Kotagiri Venkateswara Rao, while the director of photography was K. K. Senthil Kumar. The dialogue for the Telugu and Tamil versions was written by Janardhana Maharshi and Crazy Mohan, respectively. The plot of the movie takes the shape of a father reading his daughter a bedtime story. Its main character Nani, who is in love with his next-door neighbor Bindu, is killed by wealthy industrialist Sudeep, who has feelings for Bindu and sees Nani as a rival. In an effort to revenge for his death and defend Bindu from the obsessive Sudeep, Nani reincarnates as a housefly. The movie's two versions, together with a Malayalam-dubbed version titled Eecha, were released on July 6, 2012, in roughly 1,100 theatres around the world. Upon its debut, the cast's performances, Rajamouli's direction, and the visual effects all won praise from critics. One of the highest-grossing Telugu movies of the year was Eega. 7. Sivaji: The Boss 2007 action movie in Tamil that was produced and directed by AVM Productions. Rajinikanth and Shriya Saran are the movie's leads, and Vivek, Suman, Manivannan, and Raghuvaran also have prominent roles. It centers around a well-established software systems architect, Sivaji, who comes home to India after ending work in the United States. He envisions returning to society and providing free medical care and educational opportunities. Adiseshan, a powerful political figure, stands in the way of his goals, though. When corruption also appears, Sivaji is forced to take on the system on his own terms. Thota Tharani served as the movie's art director, and K. V. Anand served as the film's cinematographer. A R Rahman composed the soundtrack and background music (in his 100th milestone composition). The movie, which debuted on June 15, 2007, earned favorable reviews from reviewers and went on to become a global commercial success. It then went on to win two Vijay Awards, three Filmfare Awards, and a National Film Award. The movie was made in 3D and released as Sivaji 3D on December 12, 2012. The runtime of the 3D version was shorter than the original, trimmed to 155 minutes. The movie was also the first in India to utilize Dolby Atmos surround sound. 8. Saaho Saaho was written and directed by Sujeeth in 2019 and is an Indian action thriller movie, 