nd it was made with a budget of 50 crore rupees ($6.6 million). Pollachi was the site of most of the filming. The film was released on 11 May 2012 and grossed over ?150 crores (US$20 million) globally, becoming one of the highest-grossing South Indian films of all time. At the 59th Filmfare Awards South, Kalyan was presented with the Filmfare Award for Best Actor - Telugu. Sardaar Gabbar Singh, the follow-up, was published in 2016. 10. Chandramukhi P. Vasu wrote and directed the 2005 Tamil-language comedy-horror movie. The movie stars Rajinikanth, Prabhu, Jyothika, Vadivelu, and Nayanthara and is a remake of Vasu's Kannada film Apthamitra (2004), which was itself a remake of the Malayalam film Manichitrathazhu (1993). Nassar, Sheela, Vijayakumar, Vinaya Prasad, Sonu Sood, Suvarna Mathew, and Vineeth also acted in the movie. The story centers on a woman who has a family-wide dissociative identity disorder and a psychiatrist who wants to solve the case at any cost. Chandramukhi is the 50th movie that Prabhu and his brother Ramkumar Ganesan have produced via Sivaji Productions. Vidyasagar wrote the background music and soundtrack CD. Sekhar V. Joseph handled the filming, and Suresh Urs handled the editing. On October 24, 2004, the first day of principal photography, it ended in March 2005. A 119-crore budget was used to produce the movie. On the eve of the Tamil New Year, on April 14, 2005, Chandramukhi was made public. With an 890-day theatrical run at Shanti Theatre, the movie was a huge financial hit. The movie received two Filmfare Awards, four Film Fans' Association Awards, and five Tamil Nadu State Film Awards. For their contributions to the movie, Jyothika and Vadivelu were both given a Kalaimamani Award. In Telugu, a stand-alone prequel called Nagavalli (2010) was produced. Next TopicBest Mutual Funds to Invest ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tuto